-- CNA returns to profit
-- 
-- Mon Feb 12, 2007 8:43am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/12/us-cnafinancial-results-idUSWEN410220070212

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - CNA Financial Corp. ( CNA.N ), one of the largest commercial insurance firms in the United States, said on Monday that it had a fourth-quarter profit compared with a loss a year ago, when it was hurt by claims from 2005's Hurricane Wilma. 


 The Chicago-based insurer, a unit of conglomerate Loews Corp. LTR.N, said net income was $329 million, or $1.22 a share, compared with a loss of $217 million, or 92 cents a share, a year earlier. Income from  continuing operations, which excludes investment gains and losses, was $248 million or $1.32 a share. Analysts on average had expected CNA to earn $1.01 a share excluding extraordinary items, according to Reuters Estimates. In the year ago fourth quarter, CNA had a loss from continuing operations of $226 million or 95 cents a share.